title: Biometrics: How Unique Are You?
description:
Do biometrics help reduce crime? Which biometric systems work and which are little more than guesswork? And what are the implications for privacy?

A lecture by Richard Harvey, IT Livery Company Professor of Information Technology
22 October 2019 6PM BST
https://www.gresham.ac.uk/lectures-and-events/biometrics

If people cannot identity themselves digitally then the digital society does not work. How do biometrics help reduce crime and is it possible to have a biometric system yet not broadcast even more personal information than we do now? There are hosts of biometric systems but which ones work and which are little more than guessing?
